ns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="miter" stroke-width="1" transform="translate(0.5 0.5)" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#ffffff"><circle data-color="color-2" cx="12" cy="12" r="4" fill="none" stroke-miterlimit="10"/><path d="M22,8v9a2,2,0,0,1-2,2H10" fill="none" stroke="#ffffff" stroke-miterlimit="10"/><path data-cap="butt" d="M2,17V8A2,2,0,0,1,4,6H7L9,3h6l2.4,3.6" fill="none" stroke="#ffffff" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="butt"/><line data-cap="butt" data-color="color-2" x1="23" y1="1" x2="1" y2="23" fill="none" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="butt"/></g></svg></span><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-toggle-icon wprm-toggle-icon-inactive"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="miter" stroke-width="1" transform="translate(0.5 0.5)" fill="#888888" stroke="#888888"><circle data-color="color-2" cx="12" cy="12" r="4" fill="none" stroke-miterlimit="10"/><path d="M22,8v9a2,2,0,0,1-2,2H10" fill="none" stroke="#888888" stroke-miterlimit="10"/><path data-cap="butt" d="M2,17V8A2,2,0,0,1,4,6H7L9,3h6l2.4,3.6" fill="none" stroke="#888888" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="butt"/><line data-cap="butt" data-color="color-2" x1="23" y1="1" x2="1" y2="23" fill="none" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="butt"/></g></svg></span></button></div>
<div id="recipe-46994-instructions" class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-recipe-46994-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe="46994"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header wprm-block-text-bold wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-none" style="">Instructions</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Carefully char your aromatics with a blowtorch or over a gas hob. Set aside. In a small pan, char your spices and add to a tea bag if you have on. If you donâ€™t have a blowtorch or flame source, you can toast your aromatics in a cast iron pan as well. </span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Charred aromatics for pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Charred aromatics for pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6203.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add the chicken, onion, ginger, and spices, and cover with water. Bring up to a boil on high heat. Once boiling, reduce to a low boil and set a timer for 25 minutes.</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Making chicken pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Making chicken pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6214.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">At the end of the 25 minutes, transfer your chicken to a large bowl and let cool. Continue cooking the soup, adding water if needed. Once the chicken is cool enough to handle, roughly remove the meat from the bones, transfer to a container and refrigerate. </span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Deboned cooked chicken | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Deboned cooked chicken | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6226.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add the bones back to soup and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes to 2 hours. More time will make a better soup.</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Making chicken pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Making chicken pho | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6252.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Let the soup cool to a safe temperature (add 1qt water to help it cool), then strain (remember to put a container under your sieve). Ensure the soup has about 3 quarts of liquid, adding water if necessary. </span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="4qt Cambro | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="4qt Cambro | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6260.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Give the pot a quick rinse, then return the soup to the pot. Heat up the soup again, then season to your liking with sugar, fish sauce, salt, and msg as desired (my recommendations are up top).</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Finished chicken pho soup | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Finished chicken pho soup | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6271.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-46994-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">To serve: quickly blanch your pho noodles according to the directions on the package, then transfer to large noodle soup bowls. Warm the chicken in the soup, then evenly divide the chicken between the bowls. Just before you&#39;re ready to eat, top with soup, thai basil, chilies, and cilantro, if using. Serve with ginger fish sauce to dip. (see below)</span></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-media wprm-recipe-instruction-image"><picture class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.webp 600w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-1024x684.webp 1024w,https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294.webp 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/webp"><source data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" type="image/jpeg"><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20600%20401'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Chicken Pho Recipe | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294.jpg 1450w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-lazy-src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.jpg"><noscript><img src="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium sp-no-webp" alt="Chicken Pho Recipe | www.iamafoodblog.com" height="401" width="600" srcset="https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-600x401.jpg 600w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://iamafoodblog.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/chicken-pho-6294.jpg 1450w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></picture></div> </li></ul></div></div>
<div id="recipe-video"></div>
<div id="recipe-46994-notes" class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-none" style="">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Serves 6 as smaller bowls, or 4 as larger bowls. Estimated nutrition assumes about 5oz of noodles per person, 1/4lb of chicken, and consuming all/most of the soup. </span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<span style="display: block;"><strong>Ginger Fish Sauce Recipe</strong></span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<span style="display: block;">2" grated ginger<br />3 tbsp sugar<br />4 cloves garlic, crushed<br />2 tbsp fish sauce<br />1-2 thai chilis (optional)<br />1/2 cup water</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<span style="display: block;">Combine all ingredients in jar, cover, and refrigerate for 30 minutes before using.</span></div></div>
<div id="recipe-46994-nutrition" class="wprm-nutrition-label-shortcode-container"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-nutrition-header wprm-block-text-bold wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-none" style="">Estimated Nutrition</h4><div class="wprm-nutrition-label-container wprm-nutrition-label-container-label" style="text-align: left;"><div class="wprm-nutrition-label" style="background-color: #ffffff;color: #000000;">
